				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: The Recommend a PC Game Thread
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1831858">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I'll start the thread off with Darkest Dungeon. Now I haven't actually played this myself. It's (I believe) in Early Access, and I've been waiting for it to be finished before I start talking about it before I realized that I can't keep treating PC games like console releases. Then I saw this video and knew I had to talk about it.<br />
<br />

<iframe class="restrain" title="YouTube video player" width="640" height="390" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/P5OTJnhfI84?wmode=opaque" frameborder="0"  allowfullscreen webkitallowfullscreen  mozallowfullscreen ></iframe>
<br />
<br />
It's a dungeon crawler rpg with gothic horror influences. I'm a big fan of this kind of art, the narration is fun, and think the mechanics look interesting. While not really shown that much in the video (I'm sure it pops up more later), there is a madness mechanic in which your party slowly becomes more and more stressed as you progress.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
